Marketing Brief -- Goodyear Tire  Rubber Co.:
   National Brand Advertising
   Will Be Increased by 30%
More than 50 commercials will be aired during the
Olympics. Goodyear said its Winter Olympics TV campaign will
cost about $6 million. The Akron, Ohio, tire company also
will advertise during other televised sporting events,
including auto races and basketball games.
   Goodyear's television advertising will be supported by an
"equally aggressive" print advertising campaign in magazines,
a spokesman said. The increased advertising shows "our
evolution to a more market-driven company," he said.